<task id="t_psdk_ref_disable-abr"> 
  <title>Configuring buffer controls with the user interface</title> 
  <shortdesc>Buffering control is enabled in the <ph conref="../../phrase_library.xml#c_psdk_phrase-library/primetime-sdk-name"/> by default. You can use
	 the 
	 <ph platform="android">Primetime Settings user interface</ph><ph
	 platform="dhls">JSON configuration file or the FlashVars</ph> to override the
	 default <ph conref="../../phrase_library.xml#c_psdk_phrase-library/primetime-sdk-name"/> behavior. 
  </shortdesc> 
  <taskbody> 
	 <context id="context_AB73AC4BB91B4E0F8A8F3F3E22FFDE47"> 
		<p platform="android">To configure buffer controls through the user
		  interface: 
		</p> 
	 </context> 
	 <steps id="steps_C7B25B7E8B394C4A820CD223364CC55F"> 
		<step id="step_50A96026A8D2422BB3D8F1E6D45340FA" platform="android"> 
		  <cmd>Open the Primetime Settings dialog. 
		  </cmd> 
		</step> 
		<step id="step_4E26FACE44D7488CABDEBA89322B70CC" platform="android"> 
		  <cmd>Select Buffer control. 
			 <draft-comment>Can someone provide a screenshot for me? thank you!
			 </draft-comment>
		  </cmd> 
		  <info> 
			 <fig id="fig_B638E8E7B60F468C92D1843A943F20CE"><image
				href="images/abr-configuration.jpg"
				id="image_CD52E8B19CDA4C98A3BCC1526833ACE2"></image> 
			 </fig> 
		  </info> 
		</step> 
		<step id="step_EDB58B5715924549B4EA7CF6167136F3" platform="android"> 
		  <cmd>Tap the Enable ON control so that it displays OFF. 
		  </cmd> 
		</step> 
	 </steps> 
  </taskbody> 
</task> 
